cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SY. 

The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks (DNN) in self-organizing networks (SON) for automating networking tasks. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category as it deals with the use of neural networks in various applications. The paper also discusses the lack of robustness of DNN against adversarial examples, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of explainable AI techniques to generate explanations of incorrect classifications suggests the involvement of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with the security aspect of SON against adversarial attacks, which falls under the scope of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
